@OMFGrhombus:  
If by looking different than the other angels of the Zendikar set you mean the halos, it is because of flavor. The angels of Zendikar with halos over their eyes have those halos there as a symbol of their blindness to the truth of the "gods" they serve, as those gods are actually Eldrazi. Linvala, [Deathless Angel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Deathless Angel), the angels on [Harmless \*\*\*ault](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Harmless ***ault) and [Induce Despair](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Induce Despair),and Zendikar angel [Iona, Shield of Emeria](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Iona, Shield of Emeria) all are without halos around their eyes because they are freed from the blindness the angels once experienced. (Source: "The Defiance of Angels" off of Daily MTG: http://www.wizards.com/Magic/Magazine/Article.aspx?x=mtg/daily/stf/86).  

